WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

00:51.217 --> 00:52.469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

00:52.552 --> 00:53.970
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:54.054 --> 00:54.971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

00:59.726 --> 01:02.771
<i>No matter how beautiful and grand</i>
<i>their lives may have been,</i>

01:03.813 --> 01:05.398
<i>the dead tell no tales.</i>

01:06.816 --> 01:08.359
<i>Thus, murderers believe</i>

01:08.443 --> 01:11.613
<i>that they can keep</i>
<i>their crimes hidden for good.</i>

01:21.247 --> 01:22.415
<i>But the problem is,</i>

01:22.499 --> 01:24.125
<i>they're wrong.</i>

01:25.251 --> 01:26.961
<i>Some things do exist</i>

01:27.045 --> 01:29.214
<i>even if they're invisible.</i>

01:30.507 --> 01:33.176
<i>They're always around us.</i>

01:34.177 --> 01:35.428
<i>Actually…</i>

01:36.471 --> 01:38.473
He came into the office…

01:38.556 --> 01:39.474
<i>They're around me.</i>

01:41.184 --> 01:42.018
<i>And unexpectedly,</i>

01:42.644 --> 01:44.479
<i>they're talkative.</i>

01:44.562 --> 01:47.857
What about it? Hear me out, Mr. Attorney!

01:47.941 --> 01:50.568
<i>Well, I understand why.</i>

01:50.652 --> 01:52.946
- <i>They have no power to take revenge.</i>
- Tell them something!

01:53.029 --> 01:54.114
<i>Nor do they know how.</i>

01:56.908 --> 01:58.618
WITNESS STAND

02:03.790 --> 02:05.708
<i>This is exactly why they need</i>

02:05.792 --> 02:07.627
<i>someone to hear their resentful stories</i>

02:07.710 --> 02:09.587
<i>and convict those who deserve punishment,</i>
<i>which is me,</i>

02:10.171 --> 02:11.172
<i>Shin I-rang.</i>

02:11.756 --> 02:12.632
Your Honor.

02:13.883 --> 02:15.093
I have an objection.

02:20.265 --> 02:21.891
The culprit…

02:21.975 --> 02:23.268
is someone else.

02:27.772 --> 02:28.773
<i>However,</i>

02:29.357 --> 02:32.110
<i>I wasn't a ghost-seeing attorney</i>
<i>from the start.</i>

02:33.736 --> 02:34.988
ONE YEAR AGO

02:35.071 --> 02:36.322
Attorney Shin I-rang.

02:36.406 --> 02:38.491
Why don't you tell us
about your strengths?

02:38.575 --> 02:40.076
EPISODE 1

02:40.160 --> 02:41.995
I have two hearts.

02:42.078 --> 02:45.707
A strong heart that allows me
to race until I win a case,

02:45.790 --> 02:47.834
and a warm heart that motivates me

02:49.377 --> 02:50.753
to create a righteous society.

02:50.837 --> 02:53.715
INTERVIEW ADMISSION TICKET
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

03:03.683 --> 03:05.310
You can just walk away.

03:07.854 --> 03:10.398
I was meaning
to walk past you today anyway.

03:10.481 --> 03:11.482
That's good, then.

03:12.233 --> 03:13.109
Go on.

03:21.451 --> 03:22.535
It's okay. Just go on.

03:26.247 --> 03:29.125
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

03:52.732 --> 03:53.566
Hi, Mom.

03:54.234 --> 03:55.318
Hey.

03:56.694 --> 03:58.404
You must be tired from work today.

03:58.488 --> 03:59.614
Not at all.

04:00.490 --> 04:02.033
I do this because I like it.

04:03.660 --> 04:04.869
Oh, this?

04:05.453 --> 04:07.789
The vegetable lady was coughing.

04:07.872 --> 04:09.332
The flu is going around these days.

04:09.415 --> 04:11.417
You're such a softie.

04:11.501 --> 04:14.337
Your older sister's shop
has tons of vegetables,

04:14.420 --> 04:15.546
and you bought extra.

04:15.630 --> 04:17.882
It's nice to have a lot of vegetables.

04:17.966 --> 04:20.385
Koreans eat too much meat. It's not good.

04:20.468 --> 04:22.762
Says someone whose mom is a butcher.

04:23.513 --> 04:25.181
What I'm trying to say is--

04:25.265 --> 04:26.849
Shut it, and just bring this over.

04:30.770 --> 04:31.604
Okay.

04:32.230 --> 04:34.023
Sir, don't get drunk like last time.

04:37.026 --> 04:38.945
- Please enjoy.
- Oh, thank you.

04:40.363 --> 04:42.782
Welcome back, my dear brother-in-law.

04:43.366 --> 04:45.285
Is it a periodic drama this time?

04:45.368 --> 04:47.453
I have as many as two lines for this role.

04:48.371 --> 04:49.831
Congratulations, my lord.

04:49.914 --> 04:51.833
Thank you.

04:51.916 --> 04:53.001
Honey.

04:53.084 --> 04:54.877
I'm on my way, my lady.

04:56.879 --> 04:59.424
Da-bong, your uncle is here.

05:01.342 --> 05:02.844
Put me down, Uncle.

05:02.927 --> 05:04.345
Look at you, brat.

05:04.429 --> 05:06.222
Choose between Carbot and me.

05:06.306 --> 05:08.349
I choose you. Happy now?

05:09.434 --> 05:10.727
Yes, happy.

05:12.562 --> 05:15.189
Why are you here again?
I told you to stop coming.

05:15.273 --> 05:17.108
I might not be able to come for real soon.

05:17.191 --> 05:18.609
I want to help out while I can.

05:18.693 --> 05:19.861
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

05:19.944 --> 05:22.822
Oh, right. How was the interview?
How did it go?

05:22.905 --> 05:24.949
Everyone seemed worried.

05:25.700 --> 05:27.660
Worried? Why?

05:27.744 --> 05:30.621
Isn't it obvious?
Words spread fast in this field.

05:30.705 --> 05:32.206
They were worried they might lose me.

05:32.290 --> 05:34.167
That means they'll hire you.

05:34.959 --> 05:36.669
I didn't get an official offer yet,

05:37.295 --> 05:38.838
but I must say it's most likely.

05:38.921 --> 05:40.298
An attorney at K and L Law Firm!

05:40.381 --> 05:43.551
What a great honor for our family!

05:44.135 --> 05:45.219
Hold on.

05:45.303 --> 05:49.015
Attention, please!

05:49.098 --> 05:50.892
Each table will have

05:50.975 --> 05:53.061
a bottle of soju on the house today!

05:53.144 --> 05:54.187
- Oh, my.
- Really?

05:54.270 --> 05:55.730
The owner's insane.

05:55.813 --> 05:56.689
Drink up!

06:00.151 --> 06:02.070
One serving of pork belly
on the house too.

06:02.153 --> 06:04.947
- Oh, goodness.
- My mother-in-law never disappoints.

06:07.575 --> 06:08.743
Just one serving, not two.

06:12.955 --> 06:14.624
- A bottle of beer, please.
- Here too.

06:15.541 --> 06:16.959
Coming right away.

06:19.295 --> 06:21.881
WE REGRET TO INFORM YOU THAT
WE WON'T MOVE FORWARD WITH YOU

06:22.465 --> 06:23.716
This can't be.

06:32.934 --> 06:33.935
Okay.

06:35.144 --> 06:36.562
I was too naive.

06:39.774 --> 06:40.775
There.

06:45.071 --> 06:46.948
WE REGRET TO INFORM YOU
OF UNFORTUNATE NEWS

06:47.031 --> 06:48.491
Are you serious?

06:51.619 --> 06:53.162
YOUR APPLICATION
WAS NOT SELECTED

06:53.746 --> 06:55.623
What on earth is the problem?

07:01.921 --> 07:03.548
LAWSUIT FOR DAMAGES
PLAINTIFF: SEONGHO ELECTRONICS

07:16.227 --> 07:18.312
- This is about Haeseong Trading.
- Thank you.

07:18.396 --> 07:20.731
This is the petition
for Myeongjin Construction.

07:20.815 --> 07:23.359
- I placed the materials on your desk too.
- Okay.

07:25.278 --> 07:27.488
TAEBAEK LAW FIRM
PARTNER HAN NA-HYUN

07:40.877 --> 07:42.086
Hello.

07:43.212 --> 07:46.132
Seongho Electronics' chairman
was greatly satisfied.

07:46.215 --> 07:47.967
He wants to sign a partnership with us.

07:48.050 --> 07:49.343
That's good.

07:50.094 --> 07:52.346
You seem busy. Do you want me
to interview the applicants?

07:52.430 --> 07:54.557
It's about my future associate.
I'll do it myself.

07:54.640 --> 07:56.559
I have about 20 minutes.

07:56.642 --> 07:57.852
Then, just refer to this.

07:59.145 --> 08:00.146
What is it?

08:07.111 --> 08:10.406
THE 2025 ENTRY-LEVEL
ASSOCIATE INTERVIEW

08:13.034 --> 08:14.410
INTERVIEW ADMISSION TICKET
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

08:14.494 --> 08:15.745
Next applicant, please come in.

08:15.828 --> 08:16.704
Okay.

08:23.002 --> 08:25.379
INTERVIEW ROOM

08:32.470 --> 08:34.805
Hello, my name is Shin I-rang.

08:34.889 --> 08:36.182
Hello, please have a seat.

08:38.142 --> 08:39.894
Attorney Han, ask questions first.

08:43.147 --> 08:44.732
I don't have any questions

08:44.815 --> 08:46.526
for Mr. Shin.

08:48.361 --> 08:51.405
I'm sure he knows why.

08:51.989 --> 08:52.823
Let's move on.

08:55.243 --> 08:56.911
He's the last applicant.

09:18.516 --> 09:19.517
What are you doing?

09:20.101 --> 09:21.769
Let me ask the same question.

09:27.358 --> 09:28.609
A scarlet letter…

09:29.944 --> 09:31.237
As expected.

09:41.372 --> 09:43.874
Were you aware
of your husband's corruption?

09:43.958 --> 09:45.793
What do you think you're doing?

09:45.876 --> 09:48.004
Have you no manners at all?

09:48.087 --> 09:50.631
- Do you admit to his crimes?
- Get out.

09:50.715 --> 09:53.884
My dad wasn't a criminal.

09:53.968 --> 09:56.512
He was a prosecutor
who punished bad people!

10:07.732 --> 10:08.691
I'm turning you down.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.360
I am…

10:12.903 --> 10:14.363
turning you down first.

10:29.462 --> 10:31.422
You should've at least asked
routine questions.

10:33.341 --> 10:35.635
He needs to know how the world sees him.

10:37.428 --> 10:39.221
Only then, he'll stop biting on granite.

10:42.600 --> 10:43.809
I'll be off since we're done.

10:51.233 --> 10:54.111
A father's actions from 20 years ago

10:54.195 --> 10:55.780
is causing harm to his son.

10:56.447 --> 10:57.865
How cruel.

10:58.491 --> 11:01.619
Is it because the judge and prosecutor
related to it haven't retired yet?

11:02.286 --> 11:03.579
Maybe.

11:05.956 --> 11:07.875
This won't do. Just change your name.

11:08.584 --> 11:11.420
Put all the past behind you
and make a new start with a new--

11:13.130 --> 11:14.298
No.

11:14.382 --> 11:17.301
Now that I know how the world sees me,

11:18.844 --> 11:20.262
I won't stay still.

11:21.931 --> 11:22.765
You know what?

11:24.392 --> 11:28.437
I'm going to make the best law firm ever
under my own name.

11:30.314 --> 11:31.273
<i>And then,</i>

11:32.108 --> 11:36.112
<i>I'm going to have all those</i>
<i>who mistreated me line up in two rows.</i>

11:40.908 --> 11:43.494
<i>I'll take good revenge on them.</i>

11:43.577 --> 11:44.578
<i>Wait and see.</i>

11:59.468 --> 12:00.469
What?

12:01.762 --> 12:05.349
Are you pleased
to have ruined your son's future?

12:07.184 --> 12:08.185
Fine.

12:08.978 --> 12:12.273
Let's see who wins.

12:13.149 --> 12:14.150
Bring it on!

13:30.851 --> 13:34.563
EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICES

13:39.235 --> 13:42.238
MR. KIM'S REAL ESTATE OFFICE

13:48.536 --> 13:50.246
4,305,100 WON

13:50.829 --> 13:52.039
Would this be enough?

14:01.340 --> 14:02.716
What brings you here, I-rang?

14:04.677 --> 14:06.303
The thing is…

14:07.721 --> 14:09.974
Your mother must've sent you.

14:10.057 --> 14:10.975
What?

14:11.809 --> 14:13.227
After all,

14:13.310 --> 14:15.312
an attorney should
take charge of a contract.

14:16.188 --> 14:19.191
Please do the rest, okay?

14:19.275 --> 14:21.652
Where's Mr. Kim, though?

14:21.735 --> 14:22.736
Oh.

14:23.279 --> 14:24.780
Someone passed out or something.

14:24.864 --> 14:26.532
He'll be back soon.

14:26.615 --> 14:27.658
I'm a detective this time.

14:28.450 --> 14:29.493
See you.

14:38.294 --> 14:40.296
This must be Mom's lease contract.

14:40.963 --> 14:42.047
COMMERCIAL LEASE AGREEMENT

14:42.131 --> 14:43.340
The deposit's 200 million won?

14:45.175 --> 14:46.844
I didn't know Mom was this rich.

14:47.761 --> 14:48.762
Hold on.

14:49.805 --> 14:50.806
Two hundred million won?

14:53.809 --> 14:56.562
Why be a shaman
if you can't even tell your own future?

14:56.645 --> 14:57.980
Hello.

14:58.063 --> 14:59.398
Oh, my.

14:59.481 --> 15:01.317
What brings you here, Mr. Attorney?

15:01.400 --> 15:03.110
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

15:03.193 --> 15:05.237
Are you here to renew
the butcher shop contract?

15:07.114 --> 15:08.365
The thing is,

15:08.449 --> 15:11.076
were you the landlord of my mom's shop?

15:11.660 --> 15:12.494
You didn't know?

15:14.663 --> 15:17.041
Mr. Kim, I need your help.

15:17.750 --> 15:18.959
You need <i>my</i> help?

15:19.043 --> 15:21.337
I need to open a law office,

15:21.420 --> 15:24.632
so please let me use 30 million won
from her deposit.

15:25.215 --> 15:26.717
What?

15:26.800 --> 15:28.302
That's out of the question.

15:29.720 --> 15:31.513
I'll pay 10% more of the commission.

15:32.598 --> 15:35.351
- And I'll provide you with legal services.
- Indefinitely?

15:38.145 --> 15:39.772
- Deal.
- What's the condition?

15:40.356 --> 15:41.899
I'd like a courthouse view.

15:42.483 --> 15:43.984
A close-up courthouse view.

15:44.068 --> 15:47.404
You can't rent out an office like that
with a 30-million-won deposit.

15:48.656 --> 15:49.657
Is that so?

15:51.075 --> 15:52.076
I-rang.

15:53.118 --> 15:54.244
There may be one.

15:55.496 --> 15:56.330
Really?

15:56.413 --> 15:57.247
Yes.

15:57.331 --> 16:00.709
OPEN

16:11.303 --> 16:12.972
Come on. You're young enough for this.

16:13.055 --> 16:15.224
It's a quiet neighborhood.

16:15.307 --> 16:16.350
Over there.

16:19.812 --> 16:22.648
This is the one right here.

16:22.731 --> 16:23.732
OKCHEON BUILDING

16:25.651 --> 16:28.362
I didn't know this neighborhood
had a building like this.

16:29.655 --> 16:32.032
Oh, perfect.
The wallpapering must be over.

16:32.116 --> 16:33.283
- Mr. Park!
- Hello.

16:33.367 --> 16:34.618
I appreciate the hard work.

16:34.702 --> 16:36.662
We're all done. Thank you.

16:37.705 --> 16:38.831
Come along.

16:45.921 --> 16:48.757
All of this will get moved out.

16:52.386 --> 16:53.971
- It's here.
- Here?

16:54.054 --> 16:56.223
FOR LEASE

17:07.234 --> 17:08.736
The interior is quite unique.

17:09.319 --> 17:10.696
The landlord has elegant taste.

17:15.868 --> 17:19.204
Oh, these.
The former tenant left them behind.

17:19.288 --> 17:21.206
I'll throw them out, so don't bother.

17:21.290 --> 17:23.167
You can leave them here.

17:23.250 --> 17:24.668
It takes work to throw them out.

17:25.669 --> 17:26.962
Let's save the Earth.

17:30.466 --> 17:33.218
Anyway, what was this place?

17:34.344 --> 17:35.888
- A Chinese restaurant?
- What?

17:35.971 --> 17:38.724
Oh, what's the word?

17:39.266 --> 17:41.685
You know,
something about foreseeing the future…

17:42.728 --> 17:44.521
An AI company? Big data?

17:44.605 --> 17:45.439
What?

17:46.440 --> 17:49.234
Yeah, I think it was something like that.

17:52.237 --> 17:55.115
Don't you smell something weird?

17:56.158 --> 17:57.743
It's coming from the wallpaper.

17:57.826 --> 17:59.578
It will go away soon. Don't bother it.

18:01.455 --> 18:04.458
There's no place like this
in the neighborhood.

18:04.541 --> 18:06.919
The heavens really helped you out here.

18:07.002 --> 18:08.712
You may trick a ghost, but not me.

18:08.796 --> 18:10.714
I know there are
many empty offices these days.

18:12.674 --> 18:14.468
Wait, I-rang.

18:14.551 --> 18:15.969
You wanted a view, didn't you?

18:16.637 --> 18:17.721
Come here.

18:24.269 --> 18:25.395
Isn't it nice?

18:26.313 --> 18:27.481
Breathtaking, right?

18:58.387 --> 19:01.765
There's no other place with a
courthouse view like this at your budget.

19:01.849 --> 19:03.433
Think wisely.

19:05.477 --> 19:06.687
I'll take it.

19:06.770 --> 19:07.813
I like it.

19:13.235 --> 19:15.487
Good thinking.

19:17.656 --> 19:19.408
Yahoo.

19:24.413 --> 19:27.291
Please place it all the way
at the top of the building

19:27.374 --> 19:29.084
so that it's visible from the courthouse.

19:32.754 --> 19:35.257
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

19:49.938 --> 19:52.232
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

19:52.316 --> 19:55.652
It sure is in my blood to run a business.

20:06.580 --> 20:07.581
What was that?

20:15.672 --> 20:16.840
What is this?

20:34.191 --> 20:35.192
Is this incense?

20:37.236 --> 20:39.571
Nice. The air was musty anyway.

20:52.000 --> 20:53.085
I like it.

21:27.035 --> 21:28.036
Huh?

21:28.996 --> 21:29.997
Was it a dream?

21:35.752 --> 21:36.753
Hi.

21:36.837 --> 21:38.088
Hi, I-rang.

21:38.171 --> 21:39.506
Remember the man you mentioned?

21:39.589 --> 21:40.924
Man?

21:41.008 --> 21:42.009
Who?

21:42.092 --> 21:44.303
<i>You asked me to set you up</i>
<i>with a paralegal.</i>

21:44.386 --> 21:46.096
He's already here.

21:46.179 --> 21:47.764
Let me call you later.

21:47.848 --> 21:49.266
What… Hello?

21:50.183 --> 21:52.811
No, he's already hired.
That's why I called.

21:52.894 --> 21:54.229
He came? Who is he talking about?

21:55.480 --> 21:56.481
You're here early.

21:57.482 --> 21:58.567
You must've waited long.

21:58.650 --> 22:00.652
I don't usually sleep in like that

22:00.736 --> 22:02.487
but I've been stressed out lately.

22:04.531 --> 22:05.907
You can see me?

22:06.700 --> 22:07.701
Pardon?

22:07.784 --> 22:09.745
Yes, that's why I'm talking to you.

22:15.834 --> 22:18.962
I'm quite tall myself,

22:19.046 --> 22:20.505
but you're really tall.

22:21.840 --> 22:22.883
Are you 190 cm tall?

22:22.966 --> 22:24.301
Maybe 2 m?

22:41.735 --> 22:42.736
Y-You…

22:42.819 --> 22:44.488
W-What is it?

22:44.571 --> 22:46.239
G-Ghost…

22:51.161 --> 22:52.162
Ghost!

22:52.245 --> 22:53.872
- It's a ghost!
- Oh, dear.

22:57.542 --> 22:59.836
Dear God, Jesus Christ, and Virgin Mary,
please forgive me.

23:00.337 --> 23:03.090
I'll pay off Mom's deposit
and turn over a new leaf.

23:03.173 --> 23:05.008
Please don't let me die.

23:06.009 --> 23:07.135
What are you doing?

23:07.219 --> 23:08.595
Do you want to play hide-and-seek?

23:10.722 --> 23:13.266
Oh, my. That must be painful.

23:14.017 --> 23:16.770
Go away! Go!

23:16.853 --> 23:17.854
Go away…

23:59.980 --> 24:01.356
An AI company?

24:01.439 --> 24:02.816
Big data?

24:04.568 --> 24:05.902
He lied to me.

24:10.240 --> 24:11.241
I can't believe this.

24:13.201 --> 24:14.411
Look.

24:14.995 --> 24:17.414
Ghosts don't exist,
especially in this day and age.

24:17.497 --> 24:19.541
A shaman must've summoned him.

24:19.624 --> 24:21.001
What shaman?

24:23.003 --> 24:25.255
Fine, here.

24:26.006 --> 24:27.841
This is the evidence.

24:28.383 --> 24:31.094
You deceived me into signing this lease,
so call it off.

24:31.178 --> 24:32.637
Nowhere in real estate law

24:32.721 --> 24:36.683
is there an obligation to notify
who the former tenant was.

24:38.768 --> 24:39.769
There's more.

24:40.270 --> 24:42.480
Article 4, Paragraph 5
of the contract says,

24:42.564 --> 24:45.525
"The tenant may cancel the contract

24:45.609 --> 24:48.028
if they have not been notified
of any undesirable facility."

24:48.111 --> 24:50.822
A haunted place is clearly
an undesirable facility.

24:51.823 --> 24:53.408
So, you'll go by the book?

24:53.491 --> 24:56.286
Then, prove that there are ghosts here.

24:56.369 --> 24:57.370
Unbelievable.

25:00.123 --> 25:01.791
There he is. He's here.

25:01.875 --> 25:02.876
Over there.

25:02.959 --> 25:03.793
Where?

25:05.378 --> 25:06.421
There!

25:06.504 --> 25:08.131
There. He's there!

25:08.215 --> 25:09.716
Where?

25:09.799 --> 25:10.842
Do you really not see him?

25:10.926 --> 25:12.761
See what?

25:13.345 --> 25:14.930
Snap out of it, I-rang.

25:15.472 --> 25:16.431
What a shame.

25:16.514 --> 25:18.516
This is driving me nuts!

25:22.437 --> 25:23.730
Maybe that's it.

25:23.813 --> 25:25.106
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

25:28.860 --> 25:31.071
<i>There's this tale</i>
<i>called the Legend of Arang.</i>

25:31.738 --> 25:33.949
<i>Every time a new district magistrate</i>
<i>is appointed,</i>

25:34.032 --> 25:36.576
<i>a resentful virgin ghost visits him.</i>

25:37.369 --> 25:40.705
<i>And it kills all the feeble magistrates.</i>

25:46.836 --> 25:47.796
This is killing me.

25:49.339 --> 25:50.674
Wake up.

25:50.757 --> 25:51.758
It's a dream.

25:54.970 --> 25:56.179
<i>But then,</i>

25:56.263 --> 25:59.015
- <i>a brave magistrate survives…</i>
- Hear me out!

25:59.099 --> 26:01.726
<i>…and helps her</i>
<i>resolve her resentment at last</i>

26:01.810 --> 26:05.146
<i>in this beautiful tale.</i>

26:07.190 --> 26:08.900
Beautiful, my foot.

26:10.402 --> 26:12.654
What are you looking at?
You're not even a virgin ghost.

26:13.446 --> 26:14.322
I'm sorry.

26:15.490 --> 26:16.616
He spoke.

26:16.700 --> 26:19.411
Mr. Kim, did you hear him?
He spoke just now.

26:20.203 --> 26:21.788
Wow.

26:21.871 --> 26:24.082
You're good at acting.

26:26.167 --> 26:28.253
Still, no. I won't back down.

26:28.336 --> 26:29.170
Neither will I.

26:29.254 --> 26:31.965
I absolutely will not use this office.

26:32.048 --> 26:34.426
If you refuse, I'll take you to court.

26:35.051 --> 26:36.594
That leaves me no choice,

26:36.678 --> 26:38.346
but to discuss this with Ms. Park.

26:38.847 --> 26:40.473
I wonder if she's done butchering.

26:40.557 --> 26:42.350
I hope she has some energy left.

26:45.020 --> 26:47.981
Who scares you more? Ghosts or your mom?

27:01.119 --> 27:04.873
I'll give you a few days
until rent is due, okay?

27:09.878 --> 27:11.379
Wait for me, Mr. Kim!

27:16.926 --> 27:18.595
You have until tomorrow to leave.

27:18.678 --> 27:19.804
Otherwise,

27:19.888 --> 27:21.723
I'll come with a cross and a Bible.

27:29.189 --> 27:32.400
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

27:33.151 --> 27:34.027
Eat up.

27:34.861 --> 27:36.404
Uncle!

27:36.488 --> 27:37.947
Hi, Da-bong.

27:38.031 --> 27:41.368
You always come
every time we're having something yummy.

27:41.451 --> 27:42.619
Da-bong.

27:42.702 --> 27:44.162
Were you eating a lot?

27:44.245 --> 27:47.082
I expected you'd have dinner outside
and didn't prepare your share.

27:47.165 --> 27:49.000
It's okay.
I'll just have what's on the table.

27:49.793 --> 27:51.461
- Hold on.
- Well…

27:55.382 --> 27:56.299
You must be tired.

27:57.008 --> 27:59.094
- Let me go make some stew.
- Thanks.

27:59.177 --> 28:01.554
Have some of this first.

28:03.014 --> 28:04.391
Goodness.

28:04.933 --> 28:07.519
Uncle, why aren't you having pork belly?

28:07.602 --> 28:08.770
It's delicious.

28:09.979 --> 28:11.231
I'm allergic to pork.

28:11.314 --> 28:12.357
If I have pork belly…

28:12.440 --> 28:13.608
Then, what?

28:33.336 --> 28:35.171
Goodness, it's…

28:36.214 --> 28:37.507
It's needless to say.

28:38.967 --> 28:40.218
This is to die for.

28:47.058 --> 28:48.226
You…

28:48.810 --> 28:50.061
What?

28:50.145 --> 28:51.271
What are you looking at?

28:51.354 --> 28:53.440
Have you never seen
someone eat meat or what?

28:53.523 --> 28:54.983
That's right.

28:55.066 --> 28:57.068
I've never seen Shin I-rang have meat!

28:58.027 --> 28:58.903
Uncle.

28:58.987 --> 29:00.697
Your cheeks are red.

29:00.780 --> 29:02.282
Just like a monkey's butt.

29:02.365 --> 29:03.199
What?

29:03.908 --> 29:04.743
What about my cheeks?

29:04.826 --> 29:06.703
Hey! Hey, you brat.

29:07.954 --> 29:10.832
You shouldn't be eating pork!
Or you'll get rashes.

29:11.332 --> 29:14.169
Look at your face. It's already red.

29:19.883 --> 29:22.218
- I-rang.
- Unbelievable.

29:24.179 --> 29:26.765
Just why are you doing this to me?!

29:27.515 --> 29:29.642
Why do you have to give me a hard time?

29:30.143 --> 29:32.812
Please leave me be!

29:34.105 --> 29:38.276
"He was with the wild animals,

29:39.277 --> 29:42.405
and angels…

29:43.740 --> 29:44.783
attended him."

29:46.326 --> 29:48.036
"After John was put"--

29:50.121 --> 29:51.706
What do you want from me?

29:51.790 --> 29:53.917
Who are you in the first place?

29:54.501 --> 29:55.376
I don't know myself.

29:55.460 --> 29:57.545
This is insane.

29:58.463 --> 30:00.590
Look. Since you're an attorney,

30:01.341 --> 30:03.134
can't you look into who I am?

30:03.218 --> 30:04.219
Why should I do that?

30:04.803 --> 30:07.388
I have to pay rent starting next month.

30:08.181 --> 30:10.141
Otherwise, my mom will kill me.

30:10.642 --> 30:12.685
Bring me money or…

30:13.269 --> 30:14.854
get me winning lottery numbers.

30:14.938 --> 30:17.232
If I had such power,

30:17.315 --> 30:20.235
I would've bought a building
in the other world.

30:20.318 --> 30:22.946
Is all you can do startling me, then?

30:23.988 --> 30:25.406
How pathetic.

30:28.535 --> 30:29.828
<i>A ghost?</i>

30:30.411 --> 30:32.247
I think I got possessed
at a shaman's house.

30:33.206 --> 30:36.334
That shaman had been taken to a hospital,
but he was nowhere to be found.

30:37.001 --> 30:38.837
He ran off
without paying the hospital fee.

30:39.838 --> 30:41.798
How did you come to see that ghost?

30:42.382 --> 30:44.801
There was a desk that used to be his.

30:45.385 --> 30:47.720
I found an old incense burner
in the drawer.

30:52.642 --> 30:53.685
It's cold.

30:58.231 --> 30:59.357
That's cold.

31:00.066 --> 31:00.900
How strange.

31:01.484 --> 31:04.529
In most cases, the body twists
or the holy water makes smoke.

31:05.154 --> 31:07.073
This is not an ordinary ghost.

31:07.156 --> 31:09.325
He reads the Bible,
and he enjoys eating pork belly with soju…

31:09.409 --> 31:11.286
He even drinks coffee.

31:11.369 --> 31:12.829
Maybe he used to like having those.

31:12.912 --> 31:14.581
Being possessed

31:14.664 --> 31:17.083
manifests when their desires reach a peak.

31:17.959 --> 31:21.421
When something triggers a rush of joy,
like their favorite food or song,

31:21.504 --> 31:22.589
or oppositely,

31:22.672 --> 31:24.382
when they're faced with someone they hate

31:24.465 --> 31:26.467
or something that causes rage,

31:26.551 --> 31:27.844
the possibility of possession increases.

31:28.928 --> 31:30.430
Once you're possessed,

31:30.513 --> 31:32.765
you'd make absurd behaviors

31:32.849 --> 31:35.351
while you don't even remember

31:36.561 --> 31:37.937
what you've even done.

31:38.021 --> 31:39.856
That means I'm in a dangerous situation.

31:39.939 --> 31:40.982
Whether you are or not,

31:41.608 --> 31:44.777
let's go to Okcheon Building and check.

31:48.197 --> 31:49.741
Seriously!

31:53.494 --> 31:54.787
This is as expected.

31:55.705 --> 31:58.666
These talismans are summoning ghosts.

31:59.626 --> 32:02.253
If I burn the talismans,

32:02.337 --> 32:03.463
will the ghost disappear?

32:04.923 --> 32:05.757
Probably.

32:06.799 --> 32:07.842
No.

32:07.926 --> 32:09.802
Never, not until I find out who I am!

32:09.886 --> 32:11.679
You don't have a say here.

32:13.598 --> 32:15.475
Is he here right now? What did he say?

32:15.558 --> 32:16.851
What is he claiming?

32:16.935 --> 32:19.729
He's been grilling me
to find out who he is.

32:19.812 --> 32:22.190
Then, why don't you
look into who this ghost is?

32:22.774 --> 32:24.984
It's easy to help a spirit pass on
if you know their story.

32:25.068 --> 32:28.154
Do it for me. Do it!

32:28.237 --> 32:29.072
Do it…

32:30.615 --> 32:32.951
Even if I'm to help him,

32:33.034 --> 32:34.619
I don't know how.

32:34.702 --> 32:37.038
With his name and date of birth,

32:37.121 --> 32:38.373
he'll regain his memory.

32:38.915 --> 32:39.749
Are you serious?

32:40.333 --> 32:42.877
How do you know that?

32:42.961 --> 32:44.128
Oh, I was…

32:45.421 --> 32:47.590
once a shaman.

32:55.932 --> 32:58.810
And God's embrace has changed me

33:00.061 --> 33:01.396
like this.

33:05.692 --> 33:08.903
Come to think of it,
it won't be hard to find out who he is.

33:09.779 --> 33:12.240
You just need to check it
with whoever visited the shaman.

33:12.323 --> 33:14.867
That person must've wanted
to summon the ghost.

33:14.951 --> 33:16.035
I see.

33:16.786 --> 33:19.038
I saw there was
a security camera in the hallway.

33:26.462 --> 33:27.714
Is this all?

33:28.548 --> 33:29.882
There aren't enough materials.

33:30.466 --> 33:31.718
We don't need materials.

33:32.468 --> 33:34.012
The bereaved want to settle.

33:35.263 --> 33:36.723
I just want you to follow up on it.

33:36.806 --> 33:39.142
Well, a peaceful settlement is
the best option,

33:39.726 --> 33:41.519
but just in case it goes south,

33:41.602 --> 33:43.813
I'll make sure
to get the bereaved's signature.

33:44.439 --> 33:45.481
That sounds better.

33:49.694 --> 33:51.529
SARANG VOLUNTEERS

33:53.072 --> 33:55.033
This woman was the last visitor.

33:55.575 --> 33:56.701
Look here.

33:57.493 --> 33:59.245
She visited several times.

33:59.954 --> 34:02.498
Sir, when was this captured?

34:03.166 --> 34:04.083
Oh, that?

34:04.167 --> 34:05.418
That's a live feed.

34:05.501 --> 34:06.627
What?

34:06.711 --> 34:10.715
I'm saying that the woman is standing
in front of Unit 501 right now.

34:16.679 --> 34:18.723
How may I help you?

34:18.806 --> 34:20.266
Well…

34:21.434 --> 34:24.729
It was a male shaman's place
until recently…

34:25.897 --> 34:28.524
The shaman left due to illness.

34:29.192 --> 34:30.193
Yes, I know.

34:30.693 --> 34:34.280
I was with him when he passed out.

34:38.493 --> 34:40.328
<i>I called an ambulance too.</i>

34:41.537 --> 34:43.623
I came out of concern

34:43.706 --> 34:47.335
and decided to enter because it was
changed to an attorney's office.

34:49.295 --> 34:53.466
Did you perhaps visit the shaman
regarding your husband?

34:54.509 --> 34:56.135
How did you know?

34:56.219 --> 34:58.554
Go ahead and tell me what happened.

34:59.931 --> 35:03.267
Both attorneys and shamans are there
to hear stories of those who were wronged.

35:09.065 --> 35:10.024
A few months…

35:12.777 --> 35:13.820
A few months ago,

35:15.113 --> 35:19.242
my husband had surgery
at Cheongil Hospital.

35:20.201 --> 35:21.327
He went into shock

35:22.036 --> 35:23.621
during the surgery.

35:24.664 --> 35:27.917
Is that why you visited the shaman?

35:28.501 --> 35:30.378
To say your last goodbye?

35:30.461 --> 35:31.504
No.

35:32.922 --> 35:34.006
Since then,

35:36.175 --> 35:38.177
my daughter won't come out of her room.

35:42.014 --> 35:42.974
Open the door.

35:43.891 --> 35:46.561
- <i>Her healthy dad died out of the blue.</i>
- Open up.

35:47.854 --> 35:49.105
<i>It must've shocked her badly.</i>

35:49.188 --> 35:50.523
Come on, say something.

35:57.196 --> 35:58.072
Ji-woo!

36:01.159 --> 36:04.162
I won't do it again, so please…

36:12.128 --> 36:14.714
<i>She's locked herself in her room</i>
<i>for five months.</i>

36:16.424 --> 36:17.508
<i>I've tried to persuade her</i>

36:18.551 --> 36:21.387
<i>softly, with anger, and in tears.</i>

36:23.431 --> 36:24.640
<i>But none of it worked.</i>

36:29.687 --> 36:30.521
At least,

36:32.398 --> 36:33.900
it feels a little better

36:34.859 --> 36:36.235
to open up to you like this.

36:38.571 --> 36:39.739
Thank you.

36:42.408 --> 36:45.286
M-My name. My name and date of birth.

36:46.287 --> 36:47.538
Could you tell me

36:49.624 --> 36:52.585
your husband's name and date of birth?

36:53.252 --> 36:55.838
His name is Lee Gang-pung.

36:57.423 --> 36:58.883
He was born

37:00.092 --> 37:02.178
on April 25, 1980.

37:22.657 --> 37:24.659
My dear puppy is awake.

37:32.041 --> 37:33.584
You're pretty just like your mom.

37:34.627 --> 37:36.170
<i>I'm a dad now.</i>

37:42.551 --> 37:44.011
Thank you.

37:44.095 --> 37:45.888
Look. You're like a newlywed.

37:45.972 --> 37:47.223
Careful.

37:47.306 --> 37:48.766
SARANG VOLUNTEERS

37:51.352 --> 37:52.311
Bingo!

37:52.395 --> 37:53.229
What do you think?

38:10.288 --> 38:11.205
Min-ju!

38:20.172 --> 38:21.299
You must've

38:22.341 --> 38:25.052
struggled so much alone.

38:37.398 --> 38:38.482
Are you out of your mind?

38:46.782 --> 38:48.701
Why did she slap me?

39:05.509 --> 39:08.512
What happened all of a sudden?

39:09.096 --> 39:09.972
I…

39:11.682 --> 39:12.808
remembered.

39:14.769 --> 39:15.770
Really?

39:16.395 --> 39:17.730
My death…

39:18.522 --> 39:20.941
Please administer anesthesia.

39:23.944 --> 39:25.446
He's going under.

39:33.913 --> 39:36.374
His airway is blocked.
We must perform emergency surgery now!

39:39.293 --> 39:41.253
- Damn it!
- Should we prepare for a tracheostomy?

39:41.337 --> 39:43.255
- Doctor!
- Shut up!

39:43.339 --> 39:44.757
I'll handle it, okay?

39:56.185 --> 39:57.186
Keep this a secret.

39:59.605 --> 40:02.108
We'll just say he died from shock
due to cardiac arrest.

40:05.444 --> 40:06.987
I clearly heard a voice…

40:08.989 --> 40:11.283
urging to frame it as death from shock.

40:25.423 --> 40:27.466
He never puts his clothes
in the washing machine.

40:46.360 --> 40:49.113
JOB APPLICATION
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

41:22.480 --> 41:24.064
Why aren't you asleep?

41:24.148 --> 41:25.941
Oh, I couldn't sleep.

41:27.401 --> 41:28.777
I should go to bed now.

41:29.570 --> 41:31.155
I'm going to have a drink.

41:32.156 --> 41:33.199
Care to join me?

41:34.241 --> 41:35.826
There's no drinking snack.

41:37.036 --> 41:39.038
Soju is best when you drink it neat.

41:45.002 --> 41:46.212
Cheers.

41:58.265 --> 41:59.225
Son.

42:00.184 --> 42:01.393
Is life hard these days?

42:04.355 --> 42:06.190
When was it ever not tough?

42:08.442 --> 42:10.945
It took me five years
to barely get a law license.

42:12.571 --> 42:13.656
And I barely got a job.

42:15.282 --> 42:17.618
Still, you've pulled it all through.

42:19.620 --> 42:21.580
You're right, but…

42:23.999 --> 42:27.378
How much does it cost
to open a law office?

42:29.755 --> 42:33.926
That senior of yours named Jeong-su
or whatever even bought a building.

42:34.009 --> 42:35.177
What are you saying?

42:35.886 --> 42:37.930
You said I was too soft
to run a legal office.

42:38.013 --> 42:40.891
That was to prevent you

42:40.975 --> 42:43.269
from getting ahead of yourself
in the beginning.

42:46.272 --> 42:48.023
We don't have the money.

42:48.107 --> 42:51.610
I can take some out of the deposit.

42:52.778 --> 42:54.863
The deposit is 200 million won.

42:54.947 --> 42:56.073
Hold on.

42:56.156 --> 42:58.075
Wait. No.

42:58.158 --> 42:59.118
Mom.

42:59.201 --> 43:01.704
I love my job right now.

43:04.540 --> 43:05.874
I-rang.

43:05.958 --> 43:06.875
Yes?

43:06.959 --> 43:09.295
You know I believe in you, right?

43:11.463 --> 43:13.299
Yes, I do.

43:13.382 --> 43:15.718
I'm not sure what's concerning you,

43:17.011 --> 43:18.429
but do what you want.

43:18.512 --> 43:20.055
I've got your back.

43:23.225 --> 43:25.269
Goodness, Mom.

43:26.228 --> 43:27.771
You're drunk after one glass of soju.

43:29.356 --> 43:31.609
Okay. Go to sleep now.

43:32.651 --> 43:33.527
I will.

43:34.069 --> 43:35.821
You should go to bed soon too.

43:35.904 --> 43:36.739
Okay.

44:06.852 --> 44:09.355
TAEBAEK LAW FIRM

44:10.272 --> 44:12.775
That's not very satisfying.

44:15.319 --> 44:17.488
Do you realize how much
I'm paying you guys?

44:18.405 --> 44:20.741
The bereaved must be
signing the agreement by now.

44:21.367 --> 44:22.284
SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT

44:22.368 --> 44:24.161
Ms. Kim, you're very lucky.

44:24.745 --> 44:27.831
The doctor didn't even kill your husband,

44:27.915 --> 44:31.085
but to take moral responsibility,
he's offering as much as 30 million won.

44:31.168 --> 44:33.671
The police investigation isn't over yet.

44:33.754 --> 44:34.880
And if it is over?

44:35.714 --> 44:36.590
Take it to court?

44:37.174 --> 44:39.218
- Yes, if needed.
- Goodness.

44:40.219 --> 44:42.429
Why would you want to complicate things?

44:43.472 --> 44:44.640
It's easier said than done.

44:44.723 --> 44:47.559
You don't know how tricky it is
to prove medical malpractice.

44:48.143 --> 44:50.646
If a single thing goes wrong,
you may even lose your house.

44:51.772 --> 44:54.024
I hear your daughter is sick.

44:54.108 --> 44:57.486
What if you end up on the street
with your sick daughter?

44:57.569 --> 44:58.654
Goodness.

44:58.737 --> 45:02.116
Attorney Han, tell me if I'm wrong.

45:04.743 --> 45:07.621
Your late husband's life
can't be measured by money,

45:07.704 --> 45:09.915
but please consider it
as a token of sincerity.

45:10.624 --> 45:13.210
Of course, the decision is up to you.

45:14.545 --> 45:15.963
Can I take a look at it?

45:16.046 --> 45:20.175
You may read it through
if you can't trust me,

45:20.259 --> 45:22.636
but would you be able to understand it?

45:24.346 --> 45:27.391
It's only natural for a settling party
to read through an agreement.

45:28.308 --> 45:29.560
Keep your manners.

45:31.145 --> 45:32.521
Actually, it's okay.

45:33.021 --> 45:34.690
I'm sure the attorney reviewed it well.

45:35.732 --> 45:38.110
Good thinking. Please sign there.

45:40.028 --> 45:42.364
KIM MIN…

45:44.324 --> 45:45.742
Excuse me for a moment.

45:49.621 --> 45:51.248
What are you doing here, Mr. Shin?

45:51.331 --> 45:52.749
You remember me.

45:52.833 --> 45:54.877
Are you Mr. Lee Jeong-seok's attorney?

45:58.589 --> 46:01.175
I hope I'm not too late.

46:01.258 --> 46:02.134
Excuse me.

46:03.010 --> 46:04.678
Oh, thank goodness.

46:04.761 --> 46:05.596
Wait.

46:05.679 --> 46:07.514
Do you know him?

46:08.557 --> 46:11.018
Who are you to--

46:11.101 --> 46:13.770
You can take time to learn about me

46:13.854 --> 46:15.981
because I'll say a few things
about you first.

46:16.732 --> 46:18.108
Attorney Byeon Seung-jun.

46:18.192 --> 46:20.861
Since graduating from the Judicial
Research and Training Institute in 2017,

46:20.944 --> 46:24.948
you worked at Taebaek
for five years and three months

46:25.032 --> 46:26.700
until July of 2022.

46:28.827 --> 46:31.246
Yes, what about it? Is there a problem?

46:31.872 --> 46:36.126
Taebaek is the dream law firm
that every attorney wants to work for.

46:36.210 --> 46:37.252
Yes, you're right.

46:37.336 --> 46:39.087
And this field is so small

46:39.171 --> 46:42.049
that you may be acquaintances
with the other party's attorney.

46:42.132 --> 46:45.093
That's honestly a little leery.

46:45.177 --> 46:46.053
So,

46:46.970 --> 46:48.514
what is your point?

46:48.597 --> 46:53.060
It turns out that Attorney Byeon
and Managing Partner Yang Do-gyeong

46:55.145 --> 46:56.813
played golf together last weekend

46:57.564 --> 46:59.191
and had a private talk afterward.

46:59.775 --> 47:01.985
Hey, are you snooping on me?

47:02.069 --> 47:02.986
Me?

47:03.070 --> 47:04.821
Of course not.

47:11.328 --> 47:12.371
Oh, my goodness!

47:14.665 --> 47:16.083
Mr. Lee, congratulations.

47:17.709 --> 47:20.963
You won free legal service
at my office's grand opening event.

47:23.757 --> 47:24.883
Mr. Attorney.

47:26.051 --> 47:28.262
I'm quite smart, so you can count on me.

47:29.096 --> 47:29.972
Thank you.

47:31.723 --> 47:32.933
But what do we do?

47:33.016 --> 47:36.061
My wife already has an attorney.

47:36.144 --> 47:37.813
I looked into it

47:37.896 --> 47:39.690
and her attorney has many issues.

47:39.773 --> 47:42.317
He will definitely not defend your wife.

47:42.901 --> 47:43.777
Then, what do we do?

47:43.860 --> 47:45.153
Isn't it obvious?

47:45.237 --> 47:46.280
We'll have him fired.

47:47.614 --> 47:50.659
Like a ghost without letting anyone know.

47:59.209 --> 48:00.419
Excuse me.

48:01.086 --> 48:02.004
What are you doing?

48:02.087 --> 48:05.716
Wait just a moment.
The real deal is about to begin.

48:07.217 --> 48:08.635
Here it is.

48:08.719 --> 48:10.929
Hello, Mr. Yang. It's me.

48:11.013 --> 48:14.766
<i>Attorneys always want</i>
<i>to leave advantageous evidence.</i>

48:14.850 --> 48:17.019
You'll wire the money
to my borrowed-name account, right?

48:17.102 --> 48:18.395
<i>Did you convince Kim Min-ju?</i>

48:19.980 --> 48:22.149
It was extremely hard
to minimize the settlement money.

48:22.232 --> 48:23.066
I mean…

48:23.150 --> 48:24.443
…<i>if not for me</i>

48:25.068 --> 48:26.987
<i>your client would've had to pay up</i>
<i>like a billion won.</i>

48:28.572 --> 48:29.531
How could you!

48:30.157 --> 48:31.158
How…

48:31.241 --> 48:34.369
This is bad enough
to lose your law license.

48:35.037 --> 48:36.288
It's not good at all.

48:36.371 --> 48:38.415
Wait.

48:38.498 --> 48:41.001
I can explain. I can explain it all.

48:41.668 --> 48:44.087
Attorney Han, where are you going?
Attorney Han.

48:46.673 --> 48:49.593
Do I have any reason left to stay here?

49:00.187 --> 49:01.813
We don't need your explanation.

49:01.897 --> 49:04.358
Pull out of this case immediately.

49:04.441 --> 49:07.778
And wire twice the commission
you've received

49:07.861 --> 49:09.404
to Ms. Kim's account.

49:10.572 --> 49:11.698
Understand?

49:15.827 --> 49:16.870
Attorney Shin.

49:18.330 --> 49:19.414
Thank you.

49:24.127 --> 49:26.338
What are you going to do now?

49:27.089 --> 49:28.465
You will file a suit, right?

49:28.965 --> 49:31.468
If I file a suit and things go wrong…

49:33.261 --> 49:36.640
Why do you think your daughter is
locking herself up in her room?

49:38.350 --> 49:39.184
Excuse me?

49:39.267 --> 49:42.896
Maybe she's mad at the current situation.

49:44.398 --> 49:47.734
It's already devastating
that her dad died of a simple operation,

49:49.403 --> 49:50.862
but her mom is about to give up

49:51.780 --> 49:53.281
even without taking it to court.

50:00.831 --> 50:01.790
I…

50:02.916 --> 50:04.084
felt the same.

50:05.919 --> 50:07.754
<i>She knows that</i>

50:08.922 --> 50:11.758
<i>her mom is suffering the most</i>
<i>from her dad's sudden death.</i>

50:12.259 --> 50:14.219
How did the interview go?

50:17.180 --> 50:19.766
Well, I think I did a good job.

50:20.809 --> 50:22.728
<i>She can't bring herself</i>
<i>to say such a thing.</i>

50:25.439 --> 50:26.773
If I were you,

50:27.691 --> 50:29.651
I'd ask Ji-woo what she thinks.

50:44.458 --> 50:47.461
JI-WOO

50:55.510 --> 50:57.220
Look, Ji-woo.

51:02.392 --> 51:04.269
What happened to your dad…

51:08.523 --> 51:09.941
wasn't an accident.

51:11.860 --> 51:15.614
His doctor made a mistake
during the operation,

51:18.158 --> 51:20.410
and it killed your dad.

51:23.038 --> 51:24.164
I want

51:25.499 --> 51:28.460
to punish the doctor
for what he did to your dad.

51:31.087 --> 51:32.506
What do you think?

52:01.910 --> 52:02.869
Win.

52:07.207 --> 52:08.166
Ji-woo.

52:09.876 --> 52:10.877
What did you say?

52:13.547 --> 52:15.215
Win the trial.

52:22.264 --> 52:23.139
Okay.

52:23.974 --> 52:26.393
I'll make sure to win

52:26.977 --> 52:32.274
and punish all those
who caused your dad's death.

52:53.128 --> 52:54.462
KIM MIN-JU

52:58.216 --> 52:59.759
Shin I-rang speaking.

53:00.343 --> 53:01.678
I'll do it.

53:01.761 --> 53:05.432
I will fight for Gang-pung and Ji-woo.

53:07.434 --> 53:08.727
You made a good decision.

53:10.061 --> 53:10.979
I will

53:12.522 --> 53:14.232
do my best to help you.

53:37.839 --> 53:38.924
I was taken here,

53:39.007 --> 53:41.259
said goodbye to my family,

53:41.343 --> 53:42.427
and entered the ER.

53:43.136 --> 53:45.680
There were about five people inside…

53:47.390 --> 53:48.683
- Hello.
- How may I help you?

53:48.767 --> 53:50.060
May I take a quick look inside?

53:50.143 --> 53:51.770
- It won't take long.
- No.

53:51.853 --> 53:53.313
- Please leave.
- Wait.

53:53.396 --> 53:54.397
- Come on.
- Leave.

53:54.481 --> 53:56.399
- Wait, I…
- We'll walk you out.

53:58.443 --> 53:59.569
I'm not a weird person!

54:07.786 --> 54:10.747
CHEONGIL HOSPITAL

54:13.041 --> 54:14.542
This won't do.

54:15.085 --> 54:16.002
No.

54:18.838 --> 54:20.256
Hello.

54:20.340 --> 54:22.676
I'm an inspector
from the Korean Hospital Association.

54:23.259 --> 54:25.553
I'm here to conduct a status survey

54:25.637 --> 54:27.681
for better working conditions
of hospital workers.

54:27.764 --> 54:29.516
I see. Please come this way.

54:29.599 --> 54:30.558
Sure.

54:35.271 --> 54:38.900
We've received a report that labor rights
aren't protected at this hospital

54:38.984 --> 54:40.610
due to the recent lack of resources.

54:41.194 --> 54:44.280
I need a list of hiring and termination
for the last six months.

54:45.407 --> 54:46.241
Well, that's…

54:48.743 --> 54:51.913
From 2019 to 2024…

54:51.997 --> 54:53.873
DREAM PRIVATE DETECTIVE AGENCY

54:57.711 --> 54:59.254
ALARM

55:16.146 --> 55:18.064
PETITION

55:38.585 --> 55:41.254
- Congratulations on your first trial!
- Congratulations on your first trial!

55:42.714 --> 55:45.508
Congrats!

55:48.219 --> 55:49.971
You'll win for sure today. You can do it!

55:50.555 --> 55:52.348
Uncle, crush them all.

55:52.891 --> 55:54.934
Da-bong, watch your language.

56:04.402 --> 56:06.154
You look amazing, my son.

56:06.237 --> 56:07.280
Good luck.

56:07.363 --> 56:09.157
And watch your manners in court.

56:10.492 --> 56:12.869
Don't you worry. I'll do well.

56:15.622 --> 56:16.956
I'm running late. See you.

56:17.040 --> 56:19.667
- Gosh, okay. We should hurry too.
- Oh, okay.

56:19.751 --> 56:21.878
Where are you all going?

56:21.961 --> 56:23.129
Isn't it obvious?

56:23.213 --> 56:25.465
We're going
to watch your first trial live.

56:25.548 --> 56:27.801
How exciting!

56:27.884 --> 56:30.053
Not you, Da-bong.
You have to go to kindergarten.

56:31.012 --> 56:33.556
Go on. We'll drop her off and follow you.

56:33.640 --> 56:36.935
- Shall we?
- Good luck, Uncle.

56:42.065 --> 56:43.191
Watch it live?

56:44.109 --> 56:45.860
This isn't the Premier League.

56:46.778 --> 56:49.280
COURT OF KOREA

56:52.117 --> 56:54.119
PLAINTIFF'S TABLE

57:01.543 --> 57:04.045
Don't worry. It will go well.

57:04.629 --> 57:05.547
Okay.

57:24.399 --> 57:25.483
I-rang.

57:30.822 --> 57:32.949
I already have enough to worry about.

57:42.333 --> 57:44.335
COURT OF KOREA

57:47.464 --> 57:49.215
<i>You better wait here, Gang-pung.</i>

57:49.299 --> 57:51.551
I can't afford to have you get worked up
during the trial.

57:54.762 --> 57:57.348
<i>I move to examine the defendant,</i>
<i>Lee Jeong-seok, himself.</i>

57:58.057 --> 57:58.975
<i>Accepted.</i>

57:59.642 --> 58:01.728
<i>Defendant, come forward</i>
<i>to the witness stand.</i>

58:09.736 --> 58:11.112
Oh, my goodness.

58:11.988 --> 58:13.948
Why did you come?
I told you to wait outside.

58:14.657 --> 58:16.784
Attorney Shin, are you okay?

58:16.868 --> 58:17.952
I solemnly swear…

58:18.036 --> 58:20.163
- My neck was itchy.
- …to speak the truth

58:20.246 --> 58:22.790
the whole truth and nothing but the truth,

58:23.416 --> 58:26.753
- and if I tell a lie…
- I remembered something I didn't tell you.

58:27.337 --> 58:28.463
Save it. I'm busy right now.

58:28.546 --> 58:30.131
I think it's important.

58:32.800 --> 58:33.968
That punk…

58:38.556 --> 58:39.974
That piece of trash.

58:40.058 --> 58:41.601
Don't get worked up.

58:42.644 --> 58:45.271
Defendant, you performed surgery
on Mr. Lee Gang-pung

58:45.355 --> 58:47.190
on October 13 last year, correct?

58:47.941 --> 58:49.150
Yes.

58:49.234 --> 58:52.028
Will you elaborate
on the situation at that time?

58:52.779 --> 58:54.822
Surgery for snoring is an easy operation.

58:55.657 --> 58:57.700
There was nothing unusual.

58:59.536 --> 59:01.454
According to the materials
from the hospital,

59:01.538 --> 59:05.291
Mr. Lee's case required a change
in the structure of his airway.

59:05.375 --> 59:07.293
Thus, general anesthesia was mandatory.

59:07.377 --> 59:08.211
That's right.

59:08.294 --> 59:10.547
But the problem was

59:10.630 --> 59:11.881
the patient's heart.

59:13.341 --> 59:14.759
That little…

59:14.842 --> 59:16.594
He's lying. It's all a lie!

59:16.678 --> 59:18.137
Calm down. No one else can hear you.

59:18.221 --> 59:19.472
I got this.

59:23.142 --> 59:24.102
That's all.

59:24.894 --> 59:27.313
Your cross, Counsel.

59:30.817 --> 59:31.901
Mr. Lee.

59:32.569 --> 59:35.613
How many nurses were present
during the operation?

59:37.991 --> 59:38.866
Two.

59:38.950 --> 59:41.369
Come on. You're lying.

59:41.869 --> 59:44.414
There were about five people inside.

59:44.497 --> 59:46.666
And three nurses.

59:50.044 --> 59:52.714
Aside from Kim Mi-yeong and Choi Ji-a
whom you reported to court,

59:54.924 --> 59:56.801
there was Oh Jin-suk.

59:57.552 --> 59:58.595
Pardon?

59:58.678 --> 59:59.762
Oh Jin-suk?

01:00:01.472 --> 01:00:04.267
Well… I don't know who that is.

01:00:04.350 --> 01:00:06.936
She was with you in the ER
until the very end.

01:00:07.729 --> 01:00:08.855
Good work, everyone.

01:00:08.938 --> 01:00:10.940
- Good work.
- Good work.

01:00:11.024 --> 01:00:13.359
<i>She is the witness</i>
<i>who watched what happened</i>

01:00:13.943 --> 01:00:14.944
<i>at the closest.</i>

01:00:18.656 --> 01:00:20.116
Sir, can you hear me?

01:00:20.199 --> 01:00:22.368
Sir? Sir.

01:00:23.536 --> 01:00:25.997
Darn, what's going on?

01:00:26.956 --> 01:00:29.500
His airway is blocked.
You must perform emergency surgery now!

01:00:31.169 --> 01:00:32.795
Should we prepare for a tracheostomy?

01:00:33.713 --> 01:00:35.340
- Doctor!
- Shut up!

01:00:35.423 --> 01:00:36.966
I'll handle it, okay?

01:00:44.724 --> 01:00:46.893
In case your crime got exposed,

01:00:47.685 --> 01:00:48.895
<i>you hid the only witness,</i>

01:00:49.896 --> 01:00:51.439
<i>Oh Jin-suk, out of fear.</i>

01:00:56.152 --> 01:00:57.987
I object, Your Honor.

01:00:58.988 --> 01:01:00.823
Let us hear more first.

01:01:01.407 --> 01:01:04.118
Counsel, you made
a crucial remark just now.

01:01:04.202 --> 01:01:08.456
Can we hear from Oh Jin-suk,
whom you claim to be a witness?

01:01:10.208 --> 01:01:11.292
It is

01:01:11.876 --> 01:01:13.586
not possible at the moment.

01:01:14.879 --> 01:01:19.050
The plaintiff's counsel is straying
from the point with unverified claims.

01:01:19.133 --> 01:01:22.345
Please consider
that his statement is inappropriate.

01:01:22.428 --> 01:01:23.596
Objection sustained.

01:01:24.138 --> 01:01:26.099
Counsel, speak your words carefully.

01:01:26.683 --> 01:01:27.642
Yes, Your Honor.

01:01:28.309 --> 01:01:29.435
Then today,

01:01:30.687 --> 01:01:33.856
I'd like to submit
just his facial expression as evidence.

01:01:34.649 --> 01:01:36.943
A facial expression cannot be evidence.

01:01:49.539 --> 01:01:50.498
That is all.

01:02:12.019 --> 01:02:12.854
Defendant.

01:02:13.855 --> 01:02:15.440
Does this kind of accident happen often?

01:02:16.190 --> 01:02:18.818
No, it's a rare case.

01:02:18.901 --> 01:02:21.696
Then, you must've wondered
what caused the accident.

01:02:23.406 --> 01:02:24.490
The thing is…

01:02:26.242 --> 01:02:29.078
If it's hard to speak,
should I talk on your behalf?

01:02:29.871 --> 01:02:30.872
Sure.

01:02:32.123 --> 01:02:34.625
The truth is, Lee Gang-pung was…

01:02:36.127 --> 01:02:37.545
a gangster.

01:02:38.504 --> 01:02:39.881
- What?
- A gangster?

01:02:39.964 --> 01:02:40.882
No way!

01:02:40.965 --> 01:02:42.884
- Really?
- Oh, my goodness.

01:02:45.803 --> 01:02:47.221
What is she saying?

01:02:47.305 --> 01:02:48.806
Gang-pung was a taxi driver.

01:02:50.141 --> 01:02:51.058
Your Honor.

01:02:51.559 --> 01:02:55.062
The defendant's counsel is
making up a story in this sacred court.

01:02:55.146 --> 01:02:56.022
I doubt that.

01:02:59.484 --> 01:03:01.944
Lee Gang-pung was part of the Oseong Gang

01:03:02.028 --> 01:03:03.654
- <i>in Daejeon 20 years ago.</i>
- Hello, sir!

01:03:05.072 --> 01:03:06.449
He has a prior assault conviction.

01:03:07.658 --> 01:03:09.494
And please look at his surgery scar here.

01:03:09.577 --> 01:03:11.871
He got stabbed in the right chest
at that time.

01:03:12.455 --> 01:03:14.665
A patient with the record
of a cardiac operation

01:03:14.749 --> 01:03:17.126
died of a cardiac attack
during his surgery.

01:03:17.710 --> 01:03:19.003
Is it really irrelevant?

01:03:26.344 --> 01:03:27.553
We're screwed.

01:03:30.014 --> 01:03:31.224
Your Honor.

01:03:31.307 --> 01:03:34.143
The defendant's counsel is
insulting the deceased

01:03:34.227 --> 01:03:36.062
as well as inciting hatred

01:03:36.145 --> 01:03:38.940
by showing unnecessary pictures
and overly bringing up his past.

01:03:39.023 --> 01:03:40.233
Sustained.

01:03:40.316 --> 01:03:42.193
Defendant's counsel, please watch it.

01:03:42.276 --> 01:03:45.279
I wouldn't have brought up his past

01:03:45.363 --> 01:03:47.949
if his behavior had only been in the past.

01:03:48.533 --> 01:03:51.994
But he caused a stir with violent words
and uncooperative actions

01:03:52.078 --> 01:03:54.121
during his hospitalization.

01:03:54.789 --> 01:03:55.790
That's a lie.

01:03:55.873 --> 01:03:58.876
Please tell us how he behaved
at the hospital.

01:03:59.836 --> 01:04:01.003
Patient Lee Gang-pung…

01:04:05.299 --> 01:04:06.676
spoke profanity all the time.

01:04:07.802 --> 01:04:10.555
He often scared the nurses
with intimidating behavior.

01:04:11.222 --> 01:04:14.225
I heard he did the same to his family.

01:04:18.980 --> 01:04:19.897
No.

01:04:23.609 --> 01:04:24.527
It's not true.

01:04:32.285 --> 01:04:34.620
This can't happen here.

01:04:34.704 --> 01:04:35.997
Oh, there's one more thing.

01:04:36.998 --> 01:04:38.875
I heard he abused
his middle school daughter.

01:04:39.709 --> 01:04:43.004
It caused her to have anorexia
and she's cooping herself up in her room.

01:04:43.796 --> 01:04:45.256
<i>Being possessed</i>

01:04:45.339 --> 01:04:48.217
<i>manifests when their desires reach a peak.</i>

01:04:48.885 --> 01:04:50.887
When they're faced with someone they hate

01:04:50.970 --> 01:04:53.014
or something that causes rage,

01:04:53.806 --> 01:04:56.225
the possibility of possession increases.

01:04:57.476 --> 01:04:58.477
Hey, punk.

01:04:59.061 --> 01:05:01.480
Are you out of your goddamn mind?

01:05:02.064 --> 01:05:05.610
You're running your mouth
because you see nothing, aren't you?

01:05:06.152 --> 01:05:07.737
Are those eyes for show?

01:05:07.820 --> 01:05:10.406
Then, give 'em to me instead.

01:05:11.032 --> 01:05:14.785
Goodness, this reminds me of the ol' days.

01:05:15.328 --> 01:05:16.996
I have quite a lot of experience

01:05:17.079 --> 01:05:18.247
in prison.

01:05:18.331 --> 01:05:21.959
What is he saying?
And what's wrong with his cheeks?

01:05:22.043 --> 01:05:24.045
Mom, I'm getting a feeling

01:05:24.128 --> 01:05:25.463
that something bad will happen.

01:05:26.839 --> 01:05:29.175
Plaintiff's counsel, go back to your seat.

01:05:29.258 --> 01:05:31.218
Dang it, why should I sit down?

01:05:31.302 --> 01:05:33.346
That man should be the one sitting

01:05:33.429 --> 01:05:34.430
in his coffin.

01:05:34.513 --> 01:05:39.602
Punk, how dare you mess around
with your pathetic lies?

01:05:39.685 --> 01:05:42.104
You and that little mouth of yours.
I should just…

01:06:30.194 --> 01:06:31.654
I truly hate

01:06:33.114 --> 01:06:34.699
being a ghost-seeing attorney.

01:07:07.773 --> 01:07:09.525
This happened because I was such a softie.

01:07:09.608 --> 01:07:11.527
<i>No! Not now!</i>

01:07:11.610 --> 01:07:13.821
Don't try to get in the way,
or I'll make you pay.

01:07:13.904 --> 01:07:15.614
<i>They submitted</i>
<i>a fabricated record to court.</i>

01:07:15.698 --> 01:07:16.741
<i>Search through the EMR.</i>

01:07:16.824 --> 01:07:19.452
<i>Consider yourself blessed</i>
<i>to have Attorney Han defend you.</i>

01:07:19.535 --> 01:07:21.620
Han Na-hyun would even risk her life
to win a trial.

01:07:21.704 --> 01:07:23.205
<i>I'm from the Prosecutors' Office.</i>

01:07:23.289 --> 01:07:25.166
I don't care if she's a prosecutor.
Get her.

01:07:30.046 --> 01:07:31.422
- Who are you?
- Me?

01:07:34.008 --> 01:07:36.844
<i>I'm a gangster attorney, Lee Gang-pung!</i>

01:07:37.803 --> 01:07:42.808
Subtitle translation by:
Eunjin Erica Kim
